# Database Rules

## Role

PostgreSQL is the single source of truth for persistent domain data.

## Core principles

- All domain data must be stored in backend-controlled models
- No direct DB access outside backend services
- Dream text is immutable
- Derived summaries and analyses must be stored separately from raw material

## Data ownership

Backend owns:
- users
- dreams
- sessions
- analyses
- subscriptions

## Session lifecycle contract

- Backend API layer owns DreamSession lifecycle
- Bot and Mini App must never compute session lifecycle logic
- Only backend services decide when to create or reuse a DreamSession
- Every Dream must belong to a DreamSession

## Schema rules

- Use UUID primary keys
- Always include created_at
- Prefer immutable records for analysis history
- `session_analyses` supports multiple rows per session (no unique on `session_id`)
- `analysis_threads` groups analyses over time per session

## Analysis write-state rules

- `is_latest` is WRITE-ONLY derived state
- set only in `analysis_thread_service` during insert/attach
- never computed in read endpoints (no `MAX(created_at)` on GET)
- scope: one `is_latest=true` per `thread_id` (multiple per `session_id` allowed)
- `continuation_index` is scoped per `thread_id`

## Access rules

- Only services/ layer can access DB
- routers must NOT contain DB logic

## Migrations

- All schema changes must go through Alembic
- No manual DB edits

## Anti-patterns

- bot writing to DB
- AI writing to DB directly
- frontend mutation of state

## Design philosophy

Database stores events and states, not UI logic.